find Traverse directory trees to locate files/directories matching criteria.
- Works on metadata (name, size, time, permissions) — not file contents.
find [path] [expression]
FLAGS
-Finding by Identity (-name / -iname): -name (Case-Sensitive):find . -name "report.txt" #just returns report.txt
 flag -iname (Case-Insensitive): The "i" stands for ignore case. find . -iname "*.jpg" #all matching jpg files regardless of case
-Finding by Structure (-type):type - f Regular file, -type d Directory Folders / directories -type l Symbolic link
 find . -type f -name "*.txt" # Find all .txt files
 find /var -type d -name "logs"  # Find all directories named "logs" usually easier with other flags
 find /usr -type l # Find all symlinks

